title: Northwest Stadium - Wikipedia
snippet: Northwest Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Landover, Maryland, located within the census-designated place of Summerfield 2.5 miles (4 km) east of Washington, D.C. title: Washington Commanders' home renamed Northwest Stadium - ESPN
snippet: -- The Washington Commanders have a new name for their stadium. The team secured an eight-year naming rights deal with Northwest Federal Credit Union, and their home will now be called Northwest Stadium.
